#: ../../B/Berkeley-Quality-Software.rst:5
msgid "Berkeley Quality Software"
msgstr "Berkeley Quality Software"

#: ../../B/Berkeley-Quality-Software.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../B/Berkeley-Quality-Software.rst:9
msgid ""
"(often abbreviated \"BQS\") Term used in a pejorative sense to refer to "
"software that was apparently created by rather spaced-out hackers late at "
"night to solve some unique problem. It usually has nonexistent, incomplete, "
"or incorrect documentation, has been tested on at least two examples, and "
"core dumps when anyone else attempts to use it. This term was frequently "
"applied to early versions of the :manpage:`dbx(1)` debugger. See also "
":ref:`Berzerkeley`\\."
msgstr ""
"(しばしば「BQS」と略される)どうやらかなりラリったハッカーが夜更けに何か特異な問題を解くために作ったらしいソフトウェアを指す、蔑称的な用語。たいていドキュメントが存在しないか、不完全か、誤っており、せいぜい2例でテストされただけで、他の誰かが使おうとするとコアダンプする。この用語は\\"
" :manpage:`dbx(1)`\\ デバッガの初期版によく適用された。\\ :ref:`Berzerkeley`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../B/Berkeley-Quality-Software.rst:14
msgid ""
"Note to British and Commonwealth readers: that's /berk´lee/, not /bark´lee/ "
"as in British Received Pronunciation."
msgstr "英国・英連邦の読者への注:これは英国容認発音の/bark´lee/ではなく/berk´lee/である。"
